Make sure the cluster is healthy and osd(s) are up before running this task.
@fultonj fyi, this is why orch hangs.
Applying the spec isn't a blocking operation from ansible point of view, hence if continue the ansible execution and the osds are not up yet, everything hangs.

I started using this approach:


- name: Collect the host and build the resulting host list
  set_fact:
    hosts: "{{ hosts|default([]) + [ hostvars[item].host_name ] }}"
  vars:
    host_name: |
      {% set host = 'ansible_hostname' %}
      {%   if tripleo_cephadm_fqdn|bool %}
      {%     set host = 'canonical_hostname' %}
      {%   endif %}
      {{ host }}
  with_items: "{{ groups['ceph_mon'] }}"


using a single task to select canonical vs inventory hostname, but sounds like it doesn't work (returning a list containing AnsibleUndefined as item for each position) due to this ansible bug:

